SHOW CONSTRAINTS* table_name

or 

SHOW CONSTRAINTS (table_name)

or for columns

SHOW CONSTRAINTS* table_name.column_name
example:
SHOW CONSTRAINTS* company_employees.first_name;

output:

finance> SHOW CONSTRAINTS* company_employees.first_name;
+----------------------------------------+
| first_name                             |
+----------------------------------------+
| {'company_employees_first_name_!null'} |
+----------------------------------------+

!null means NOT NULL CONSTRAINT.